<%INIT>
use RT::Interface::REST;

my $text = <<EOF;
Usage:

search                              search interface for data
search/address
search/asn                          
search/domain
search/email
search/impact
search/malware
search/malware/impact
search/malware/description
search/url (will accept md5's or sha1's)

feeds                               generate feed data, usually same as search with less duplication and removal of whitelisted items
                                    all feeds urls include feeds/<TYPE>/impact and feeds/<TYPE>/description for more advanced filtering
                                    eg: feeds/fastflux/impact/conficker, feeds/malicious_domains/impact/zeus

feeds/domain                        umbrella feed all all domain related intel
feeds/daomin/suspicious_nameservers 
feeds/domain/malicious_domains      
feeds/domain/fastflux

feeds/email                         all email address related intel

feeds/inet                          all inet (ip-address) related intel
feeds/infrastructure
feeds/suspiciousnetworks
feeds/scanners
feeds/spammers

feeds/malware                       all malware related intel

feeds/url                           all url related intel
feeds/url/malware
feeds/url/phishing

uuid                                load a specific message uuid (eg: uuid/12345678-1234-1234-1234123412341234)

Common Parameters:

apikey=(your uuid-based apikey)
format=(json|text|xml)
detecttime=('2010-06-05T00:00:00Z')

EOF

$m->out($text);
</%INIT>
